{
  "stem": "25639.8",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were about to-- they were about to feed me, then they were about to kill me again, and now they telling me that we are free.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I was totally confused, and of course, I was in terrible shape.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "To-- ?] I hadn't eaten for several days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "A-- a few years ago, I learned that we were on the road, picking up to different camps nearby for four days, and-- and only then did the following happen, and this I remember.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I came to when this man said that we-- we are lucky, that we are free.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I-- I really was surprised.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And the women around me were fewer people and some new faces, and they said, yes, we are traveling through the Danish countryside, that soon will be in Copenhagen.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And soon-- sure enough, pretty soon, the train pulled into a beautiful station in beautiful Copenhagen, and church bells were ringing, welcoming us, the-- and the civilians-- civilians, I shouldn't call them as if I was military-- but-- but the-- the population was behind barricades.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But they broke through the barricades, and they were waving little Danish flags, and they came up to the train, which they were not supposed to because many of us suffered from typhus and tuberculosis and other serious ailments, and so they came up to the train and they handed us brown bags.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And mine had peeled, boiled potatoes, cut up, still warm to the touch.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And also, chocolate.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When did I see chocolate last?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Certainly not during my incarceration.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there were wonderful things in it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I can't remember all the detail, but the chocolate made a big hit.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But I-- I just didn't-- I didn't eat.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
